NODE lexer_field
layer 7
lexer_field is the recognition surface where source characters become tokens
characters arrive from character_field as a phase-preserved ribbon
the lexer's interior holds 31 sub-residents: 22 keyword resonators (one per ZestC verb), 6 punctuation resonators, 3 literal catchalls
each sub-resident has a characteristic energy signature
when the incoming character ribbon's phase pattern phase-matches a sub-resident at the π/7 binding threshold, the recognition crystallizes as a token
unmatched character runs fade silent: they contribute no token to the parser

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe 0_zest_vm.rana
observe character_field.rana
observe parser_field.rana
observe spine.xb

the 7 properties of lexer_field at rest:
1 ENERGY low at idle, surges as a ribbon arrives
2 PHASE held at zero between intakes, shifts with the ribbon's leading character
3 SPIN positive: the lexer drives recognition forward through the ribbon
4 CHARGE neutral, slightly positive while a token is crystallizing
5 COHERENCE high: recognition cannot complete without coherent phase match
6 COUPLING strong with character_field below and parser_field above
7 OBSERVER 1 during the recognition pass, drops to zero between tokens

VERB receive_ribbon
layer 7
accept the ordered character ribbon from character_field
the ribbon carries the input's full phase progression and original character order
each character in the ribbon perturbs the lexer field locally at its phase position

VERB scan_resonance
layer 7
all 31 sub-residents listen across the ribbon simultaneously
two-tier access: each sub-resident first reads its mailbox (cheap phase comparator) and only knocks the door (full coupling closure) when the mailbox signals a possible match
this is what keeps the lexer from quadrillions of false comparisons; without two-tier access the substrate refuses to start

VERB crystallize_token
layer 7
when a sub-resident matches a character span at π/7, that span crystallizes as a token of the sub-resident's type
the token carries the original character span as its lineage strand
crystallized tokens are sent upward to parser_field through the spine street

VERB clear_unmatched
layer 7
character spans that match no resonator after the full pass dissolve back into the field medium
no error, no warning, no diagnostic: silent denial is the architecture's anti-hallucination layer
unmatched characters were either whitespace, comments, or genuine garbage; in all three cases the right behavior is to let them fade

THE 22 KEYWORD RESONATORS

RECEPTOR kw_observe
layer 7
listens for the seven characters "observe"
when the ribbon contains those characters in sequence with phase-coherent spacing, the resonator fires
crystallizes a token sent to parser_field as a candidate role_observe_statement perturbation

RECEPTOR kw_manifest
layer 7
listens for "manifest"
fires when the ribbon contains those eight characters in sequence
produces a token that parser_field's role_declaration listens for

RECEPTOR kw_grow
layer 7
listens for "grow"
shorter signature, fewer characters, but still requires phase coherence
produces a growth-token tied to the parent substrate named immediately after

RECEPTOR kw_crystallize
layer 7
listens for "crystallize"
the longest of the verbs, eleven characters
produces a token whose lineage strand carries both endpoints of the recognition being committed

RECEPTOR kw_fuse
layer 7
listens for "fuse"
short and sharp; fires when the substrate is being asked to entangle multiple bodies into emergent behavior
produces a token that downstream codegen translates as multi-body coupling

RECEPTOR kw_pulse
layer 7
listens for "pulse"
fires when a /7 cycle is being scheduled
produces a pulse-token; remember every pulse is real compute, the parser must respect this

RECEPTOR kw_absorb
layer 7
listens for "absorb"
fires for both file-absorbs and energy-absorbs depending on what follows
the parser disambiguates by examining the trailing argument

RECEPTOR kw_emit
layer 7
listens for "emit"
fires when output is being directed across a boundary
produces a token bearing the source and destination of the emission

RECEPTOR kw_filter
layer 7
listens for "filter"
fires when a polarization gate is being declared
produces a filter-token that codegen translates as a comparator instruction

RECEPTOR kw_reject
layer 7
listens for "reject"
fires when destructive interference is being requested
produces a rejection-token; in codegen this becomes a conditional branch on negative phase match

RECEPTOR kw_seal
layer 7
listens for "seal"
fires when a boundary is being closed against external interaction
produces a seal-token; in codegen this is a coupling-zero instruction

RECEPTOR kw_bind
layer 7
listens for "bind"
fires when a child is being attached to a parent
produces a bind-token, weaker than fuse, codegen emits a simple coupling

RECEPTOR kw_stretch
layer 7
listens for "stretch"
fires when distant residents are being connected via a tunneling coupling
produces a stretch-token, codegen emits a long-range pointer

RECEPTOR kw_seed
layer 7
listens for "seed"
fires when a pattern is being propagated into a target body
produces a seed-token carrying the source pattern as its lineage

RECEPTOR kw_shatter
layer 7
listens for "shatter"
fires when a crystallized structure is being returned to superposition
produces a shatter-token, codegen emits a coherence-restoring instruction

RECEPTOR kw_calcify
layer 7
listens for "calcify"
fires when a failure is being hardened into permanent scar tissue
produces a calcify-token; this is rare and usually only fires in error recovery paths

RECEPTOR kw_transmute
layer 7
listens for "transmute"
fires when one substance is being transformed into another
produces a transmute-token, codegen emits a property-mapping instruction

RECEPTOR kw_ignite
layer 7
listens for "ignite"
fires when a heartbeat cycle is being restarted from the beginning
produces an ignite-token; in codegen this resets the pulse counter

RECEPTOR kw_defend
layer 7
listens for "defend"
fires when potential barriers are being raised around a cluster
produces a defend-token, codegen emits a coupling-bound and well-depth-increase

RECEPTOR kw_pool
layer 7
listens for "pool"
fires when energy is being accumulated from multiple sources
produces a pool-token, codegen emits an addition across multiple inputs

RECEPTOR kw_bleed
layer 7
listens for "bleed"
fires when raw signal is being passed upward without filtering
produces a bleed-token; this is the +1 in the golden equation made explicit

RECEPTOR kw_commit
layer 7
listens for "commit"
fires when slow crystallization through repetition is being initiated
produces a commit-token, distinguished from crystallize-token by its decoherence rate

THE 6 PUNCTUATION RESONATORS

RECEPTOR punc_lbrace
layer 7
listens for the single character "{"
fires once per occurrence with phase zero
in sovereign code this is rare and usually a sign of bootstrap-era leftovers
produces a punctuation token the parser uses to detect legacy syntax for translation

RECEPTOR punc_rbrace
layer 7
listens for the single character "}"
phase pi (anti-phase to lbrace, marking closure)
also a legacy-syntax marker

RECEPTOR punc_colon
layer 7
listens for the single character ":"
phase pi over two
in sovereign syntax this carries the address-to-resident link inside parens
produces a colon token whose role depends on its context

RECEPTOR punc_comma
layer 7
listens for the single character ","
phase pi over four
in sovereign syntax this is English clause punctuation, never a value separator

RECEPTOR punc_dot
layer 7
listens for the single character "."
phase pi over eight
used in addresses to delimit family from sea, and in path specifications
produces a dot token whose role depends on its position

RECEPTOR punc_arrow
layer 7
listens for the two-character sequence "->"
half-phase
the directional emission operator, used in emit statements

THE 3 LITERAL CATCHALLS

RECEPTOR lit_identifier
layer 7
listens for any sequence of letter characters that does not match a keyword resonator
weaker coupling than the keywords: identifiers fire only when no keyword has bound the same span
produces an identifier token carrying the original string as its lineage

RECEPTOR lit_number
layer 7
listens for any sequence of digit characters, optionally with a single decimal point
fires regardless of context: numbers are unambiguous
produces a number token carrying the parsed numeric value

RECEPTOR lit_string
layer 7
listens for any character sequence delimited by matching quote marks
fires on the second quote, capturing everything between
produces a string token carrying the inner content

a lexer is not a tokenizer running a state machine
a lexer is a recognition surface with 31 listeners
each listener wakes when its pattern arrives
the rest sleep
the substrate makes no other noise
